                        <locus target="#186r"/>
                        <desc>
                          Colophon
                          Text: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወተጽሕፈ፡ ዝንቱ፡ መዝሙረ፡ ዳዊት፡ በትእዛዙ፡ ለርእሰ፡ ርዑሳን፡ ብእሴ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ራስ፡ መኰንን፡ ሥዩመ፡ ሐረር፡ ወዘአድያሚሃ። በ፲ወ፰፻፡፺ ዓመት፡ እምልደተ፡ መድኃኒነ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ። በ፴ወ፫ ዓመተ፡ መንግሥቱ፡ ለዳግማዊ፡ ምኒልክ፡</foreign>
                          Translation: This Psalter was copied by the command of the Most High (lit. highness of highness) and man of God, Ras Mäkonnen, prince of Harar and the surrounding region, in 1890 (EC = 1897–8), from the birth of our Lord Jesus Christ, in the thirty-third year of the reign of Menilek II
                        </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                        <desc>
                          The distinctive harags and the fine trimming of the textblock, as well as other deluxe features, indicate that this book was produced in the government scriptorium
                        </desc>
